I'd like to see a release of twine. I know a number of others would also.

Currently, I see #450 as a blocker. I'd like to get that fixed and then see a release made. Alternatively, we might consider issuing a bugfix release for #423 (excluding later commits).

@sigmavirus24 or @theacodes Do you have any plans for the timing of a release?

@sigmavirus24 do you mind releasing a new version of Twine?

Once it's released @di and I will be unblocked from merging several PRs to update docs to point to `twine check`.

I can try to take on the next release, and see if I can find some time to dedicate to release engineering here.
